body_html:
A few things

  • Could you show the exact commands you are running and their traceback? Include the install and the check import?
  • Are you using pip? Did you check the pip list. Did you check that the pip you are running corresponds to the python you are running.?
  • Try virtualenv.
  • Try what is listed here https://www.tensorflow.org/install/install_linux (under common install problems)

body:
A few things
 * Could you show the exact commands you are running and their traceback?  Include the install and the check import? 
  * Are you using pip? Did you check the `pip list`. Did you check that the pip you are running corresponds to the python you are running.?
  * Try virtualenv.
  * Try what is listed here https://www.tensorflow.org/install/install_linux (under common install problems)
